{{c1::Loop diuretics}} and {{c2::thiazide diuretics}} are 2 types of diuretics that cause alkalosis due to K excretion causing K movement out of cells in exchange for H.
Also, in low K states, H is exchanged for Na in the collecting duct instead of K.
Which serum electrolyte deficiency is associated with tetany, seizures and prolonged QT interval?{{c1::Hypocalcemia}}
{{c1::Colonic Diverticular Disease (Diverticulosis)}} is a GI disorder that involves the outpouching of mucosa into or through the muscularis propria.
